   improved frequency response model}},
Journal = {{INTERNATIONAL TRANSACTIONS ON ELECTRICAL ENERGY SYSTEMS}},
Year = {{2017}},
Volume = {{27}},
Number = {{9}},
Month = {{SEP}},
Abstract = {{Under frequency load shedding (UFLS) is an effective remedy against
   power system frequency collapses. An optimal approach for designing UFLS
   schemes of regional power system is presented in this paper. An improved
   multigenerator frequency response (IMFR) model that incorporates UFLS
   schemes is built to accurately and quickly evaluate system frequency
   after generator and load imbalance. Unlike the conventional system
   frequency response model, IMFR involves a spinning reserve, different
   types of governors, the static load model, and network influence. The
   representative operating and contingencies for designing UFLS schemes
   are selected with the use of IMFR. The optimization object function is
   defined for minimizing the amount of total load shed and considering
   UFLS design and performance criteria. Then, the optimal UFLS scheme is
   designed through IMFR and adaptive simulated annealing algorithm.
   Finally, the approach is applied to an actual regional power system in
   China. The effectiveness of the optimal UFLS scheme is investigated
   through a simulation.}},
