   modes that are important to planning and operations in this sector.
   Attention is given to the role of documents and citizen actions in the
   courts, expanding the coverage of water informality in India.
   Rent-seeking is also identified as a mode of governance. This
   qualitative examination draws from policy and official documents,
   testimonies, and citizen-justice interactions to shed light on cultural
