   occupies a singular position in the global energy system. A major
   portion of the Brazilian occupancies has electricity and the energy
   system expansion that, at first, possesses adequate means for supporting
   the economic growing may experience some turnovers. The Brazil
   determination through alternative fuels was a natural choice, given its
   large hydropower potential and land agricultural base. In the
   transportation sector Brazil has developed its energy matrix towards an
   important rate of ethanol and biodiesel. Although those fuels are low
